.TH "prepare_dma" 9 "prepare_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
prepare_dma \- This function creates and initializes the DMA chain for the request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" prepare_dma
.BI "(struct pch_udc_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "struct pch_udc_request *req "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
Reference to the endpoint structure
.IP "req" 12
Reference to the request
.IP "gfp" 12
Flag to be used while mapping the data buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return codes:
0:              Success
Other 0:        linux error number on failure
